Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BDawson's%20Creek%26quot%3B%20star%20James%20Van%20Der%20Beek%2C%2047%2C%20announced%20November%203%20that%20he%20has%20been%20diagnosed%20with%20colorectal%20cancer.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EData%20suggests%20that%20bowel%20cancers%20are%20on%20the%20rise%20among%20people%20younger%20than%2050.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EStudies%20have%20found%20that%20younger%20people%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20diagnosed%20with%20advanced%20stages%20of%20colorectal%20cancer.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ERisk%20factors%20include%20genetics%20and%20diet.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EColorectal%20cancer%20has%20become%20increasingly%20common%20in%20younger%20people%2C%20with%20one%20in%20five%20cases%20now%20diagnosed%20in%20patients%20in%20their%20early%2050s%20or%20younger%2C%20according%20to%C2%A0the%C2%A0American%20Cancer%20Society.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20rates%20are%20increasing%20in%20young%20people%2C%20but%20it's%20alarming%20to%20see%20how%20rapidly%20the%20whole%20patient%20population%20is%20shifting%20younger%2C%20despite%20shrinking%20numbers%20in%20the%20overall%20population%2C%26quot%3B%C2%A0Rebecca%20Siegel%2C%20senior%20scientific%20director%20at%20the%20American%20Cancer%20Society%2C%20and%20lead%20author%20of%20a%20report%20published%20in%202023%2C%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release.%20%26quot%3BThe%20trend%20toward%20more%20advanced%20disease%20in%20people%20of%20all%20ages%20is%20also%20surprising%20and%20should%20motivate%20everyone%2045%20and%20older%20to%20get%20screened.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20also%20found%20that%20more%20people%20are%20being%20diagnosed%20with%20late%20stages%20of%20the%20disease%3B%2060%25%20of%20cases%20were%20found%20to%20have%20spread%20to%20other%20regions%20of%20the%20body%20in%202019%2C%20up%20from%2052%25%20in%20the%20mid-2000s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20added%20to%20previous%20research%20over%20the%20past%20three%20decades%20that%20suggests%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-common-symptoms-colon-cancer-under-50s-chart-2024-5%5C%22%3Erising%20rates%20of%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20related%20illnesses%20like%20rectal%20cancer%20among%20younger%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjames-van-der-beek-has-colorectal-cancer-at-47-2024-11%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjames-van-der-beek-has-colorectal-cancer-at-47-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3EJames%20Van%20Der%20Beek%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20%26quot%3BDawson's%20Creek%26quot%3B%20fame%20announced%20on%20November%203%20that%20he%20had%20been%20diagnosed%20with%20colorectal%20cancer%20at%20age%2047.%20He%20didn't%20give%20details%20of%20his%20prognosis%20but%20told%20People%3A%20%26quot%3BThere's%20reason%20for%20optimism%2C%20and%20I'm%20feeling%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20%26quot%3BBlack%20Panther%26quot%3B%20actpr%20Chadwick%20Boseman%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchadwick-boseman-world-mourns-death-of-black-panther-star-2020-8%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchadwick-boseman-world-mourns-death-of-black-panther-star-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3E%C2%A0died%20of%20complications%20related%20to%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20age%2043%2C%20shocking%20fans%2C%20since%20he%20had%20received%20a%20stage-three%20diagnosis%20four%20years%20earlier%2C%20but%20never%20publicly%20spoken%20about%20the%20illness.%C2%A0His%20death%20was%20a%20pivotal%20moment%20in%20raising%20awareness%20of%20the%20rising%20number%20of%20younger%20people%20receiving%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fget-colonoscopy-colon-cancer-symptoms-colorectal-oncologist-2024-4%5C%22%3Ecolorectal%20cancer%20diagnosis%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20%26quot%3BBlack%20Panther%26quot%3B%20star%20%C2%A0Chadwick%20Boseman%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchadwick-boseman-world-mourns-death-of-black-panther-star-2020-8%5C%22%3Edied%20of%20complications%20related%20to%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0at%20age%2043%2C%20shocking%20fans%2C%20since%20he%20had%20received%20a%20stage-three%20diagnosis%20four%20years%20earlier%2C%20but%20never%C2%A0publicly%20spoken%20about%20the%20illness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20caught%20early%2C%20colon%20cancer%20is%20very%20treatable%2C%20and%20the%20five-year%20relative%20survival%20rate%20is%20about%2090%25%20if%20the%20cancer%20doesn't%20spread%2C%20according%20to%20the%20American%20Cancer%20Society.%20Bowel%20cancers%20can%20be%20difficult%20to%20diagnose%20because%20the%20symptoms%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20abdominal%20pain%2C%20constipation%2C%20diarrhea%2C%20weight%20loss%2C%20and%20fatigue%20%E2%80%94%20are%20common%20with%20ailments%20like%20hemorrhoids%2C%20inflammatory%20bowel%20disease%2C%20or%20irritable%20bowel%20syndrome.%20What's%20more%2C%20routine%20testing%20isn't%20offered%20to%20many%20people%20under%2050%20in%20several%20countries%2C%20including%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20common%20for%20people%20to%20have%20no%20symptoms%20until%20the%20later%20stages%20of%20the%20illness.%20That's%20why%20it's%20important%20to%20get%20screened%20regularly%2C%20especially%20if%20you%20have%20risk%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EObesity%2C%20poor%20diet%2C%20and%20genetics%20can%20all%20increase%20the%20risk%20of%20bowel%20cancers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGenetics%20is%20a%20major%20risk%20factor%20for%20colon%20cancer.%20There's%20evidence%20that%20bowel%20cancers%20are%20more%20likely%20in%20younger%20people%20with%20a%20family%20history%20of%20the%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEating%20habits%20also%20play%20a%20role%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flunches-prevent-colon-cancer-dietitian-2024-4%5C%22%3Ebowel-cancer%20risk%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20diets%20low%20in%20fiber%20and%2For%20high%20in%20red%20meat%20and%20processed%20meat%20have%20been%20linked%20to%20an%20increased%20risk%20of%20the%20disease.%20Some%20experts%20have%20hypothesized%20that%20the%20recent%20popularity%20of%20meat-heavy%20diets%20like%20keto%20and%20paleo%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-young-people-diagnosis-causes-risk-factors-2019-7%5C%22%3Epartly%20to%20blame%20for%20rising%20cancer%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EObesity%20has%20also%20been%20linked%20to%20an%20increased%20risk%20of%20bowel%20cancer%2C%20as%20have%20habits%20like%20smoking%20and%20excessive%20alcohol%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERace%20and%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStudies%20have%20found%20that%20Black%20people%20may%20be%20disproportionately%20affected%20by%20colon%20cancer%20in%20the%20US%2C%20in%20part%20because%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-racial-gap-in-coronavirus-deaths-is-driven-by-racism-2020-6%5C%22%3Eracism%20and%20barriers%20to%20getting%20medical%20treatment%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudies%20have%20also%20found%20that%20stress%20stemming%20from%20racism%20and%20the%20hurdles%20that%20Black%20people%20have%20historically%20faced%20in%20the%20US%20also%20have%20tangible%20effects%20on%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESymptoms%20like%20rectal%20bleeding%2C%20unexplained%20weight%20loss%2C%20and%20constipation%20or%20diarrhea%20can%20be%20warning%20signs%20of%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20symptoms%20of%20colon%20cancer%20can%20also%20indicate%20more%20mundane%20illnesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20changes%20in%20bowel%20movements%20like%20constipation%20or%20diarrhea%20could%20indicate%20colon%20cancer%20%E2%80%94%20but%20also%20a%20plethora%20of%20other%20ailments%2C%20including%20infections%2C%20irritable%20bowel%20syndrome%2C%20or%20inflammatory%20bowel%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbdominal%20pain%2C%20unexplained%20weight%20loss%2C%20and%20fatigue%20can%20also%20be%20symptoms%20of%20colon%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20major%20warning%20sign%20of%20colon%20cancer%20is%20rectal%20bleeding%20or%20bloody%20stool.%20While%20this%20could%20also%20be%20hemorrhoids%2C%20you%20should%20consult%20a%20medical%20professional%20if%20you%20experience%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20unique%20indicator%20of%20colon%20cancer%20is%20the%20feeling%20of%20being%20unable%20to%20empty%20the%20bowels%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Mayo%20Clinic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EColon-cancer%20treatment%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETreatment%20varies%20depending%20on%20how%20far%20the%20cancer%20has%20advanced%20and%20where%20in%20the%20bowel%20it%20is%2C%20but%20it%20can%20include%20surgery%2C%20radiation%20therapy%2C%20chemotherapy%2C%20and%20immunotherapy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first-line%20treatment%20for%20colon%20cancer%20at%20stages%20zero%20or%20one%20is%20surgery%20to%20remove%20the%20affected%20part%20of%20the%20colon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20past%20stage%20two%2C%20when%20the%20cancer%20is%20still%20localized%20but%20is%20growing%2C%20chemotherapy%20is%20considered%2C%20particularly%20if%20it%20has%20perforated%20the%20colon%20and%2For%20appears%20at%20risk%20of%20resurging%20after%20surgery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStage%20three%2C%20when%20the%20cancer%20has%20spread%20to%20nearby%20lymph%20nodes%20but%20not%20to%20other%20organs%2C%20requires%20surgery%20and%20chemotherapy%2C%20with%20additional%20radiation%20if%20the%20cancer%20is%20advancing%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20stage%20four%2C%20when%20the%20cancer%20has%20spread%20to%20other%20organs%2C%20patients%20can%20undergo%20a%20combination%20of%20chemotherapy%20and%20surgery%2C%20radiation%20therapy%2C%20and%20other%20targeted%20treatments%20to%20try%20to%20treat%20the%20cancer%20or%20to%20alleviate%20the%20pain%20associated%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEveryone%2045%20and%20older%20should%20get%20screened%20regularly%20for%20bowel%20cancer%2C%20and%20so%20should%20younger%20people%20at%20a%20higher%20risk%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBowel%20cancer%20is%20diagnosed%20with%20a%20variety%20of%20tests%2C%20including%20stool%20tests%2C%20colonoscopies%2C%20X-rays%2C%20or%20CT%20scans%20of%20the%20bowels.%20A%20regular%20physical%20exam%20can%20help%20identify%20any%20abnormalities%20and%20detect%20the%20cancer%20sooner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20Cancer%20Society%20recommends%20that%20all%20adults%20over%2045%20be%20tested%20regularly%20for%20colon%20cancer%2C%20even%20if%20they%20have%20no%20symptoms.%20People%20older%20than%2050%20are%20still%20at%20a%20greater%20risk%20of%20developing%20colon%20cancer%20overall.%20However%2C%20people%20under%2050%20are%20more%20often%20diagnosed%20with%20hard-to-treat%2C%20advanced%20forms%20of%20the%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facsjournals.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1002%2Fcncr.32347%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOne%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20involving%20more%20than%201%20million%20people%20with%20colon%20cancer%20from%202004%20to%202015%20found%20that%2051.6%25%20of%20those%20under%2050%20were%20diagnosed%20with%20stage%20three%20or%20four%20cancer%2C%20while%2040%25%20of%20people%20over%2050%20were%20diagnosed%20at%20those%20later%20stages.%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facsjournals.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1002%2Fcncr.32347%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20personal%20risk%20factors%20can%20determine%20how%20frequently%20you%20should%20be%20tested%2C%20so%20it's%20best%20to%20talk%20to%20your%20doctor%20about%20your%20health%20history%20and%20schedule%20tests%20accordingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20very%20clear%20that%20signs%20and%20symptoms%20that%20might%20indicate%20colorectal%20cancer%20in%20those%20under%2050%2C%20and%20particularly%20rectal%20bleeding%2C%20should%20be%20evaluated%20by%20a%20healthcare%20professional%20promptly%20and%20not%20dismissed%20as%20'only%20hemorrhoids'%20or%20'normal%2C'%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20David%20Greenwald%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20medicine%20and%20gastroenterology%20at%20the%20Icahn%20School%20of%20Medicine%20at%20Mount%20Sinai%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-young-people-diagnosis-causes-risk-factors-2019-7%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-know-about-colon-cancer-symptoms-diagnosis-chadwick-boseman%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730725246000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6728c4d688cea3ba1c1e0696%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-know-about-colon-cancer-symptoms-diagnosis-chadwick-boseman%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'Dawson's%20Creek'%20actor%20James%20Van%20Der%20Beek%20revealed%20he%20has%20been%20diagnosed%20with%20bowel%20cancer%2C%20a%20condition%20on%20the%20rise%20in%20younger%20people.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22amiller%40insider.com%20(Anna%20Medaris%2CGabby%20Landsverk%2CKim%20Schewitz)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-know-about-colon-cancer-symptoms-diagnosis-chadwick-boseman%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Top%205%20Bank%20FDs%3A%20Best%20FDs%20for%201%2C%202%2C%203%20and%205-year%20time%20period%3F%20Check%20list%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730725200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-114944270%2Cimgsize-70360.cms%22