C%22141d40ac-2f01-4b10-af9e-d610b85c6c03%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ECallahan%20was%20quickly%20resuscitated%2C%20but%20my%20heart%20stopped%20again%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20doctors%20were%20delivering%20Callahan%2C%20another%20team%20was%20working%20on%20me.%20I%20was%20still%20unresponsive.%20Callahan%20was%20born%20not%20breathing%2C%20but%20he%20quickly%20came%20to.%20Doctors%20told%20my%20family%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20baby%20is%20fine%2C%20but%20Kayleigh%20isn't.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDoctors%20restarted%20my%20heart%2C%20but%20it%20stopped%20again.%20My%20OB%2FGYN%20recognized%20that%20I%20was%20having%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fafesupport.org%2Fwhat-is-amniotic-fluid-embolism%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eamniotic%20fluid%20embolism%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20an%20allergic-like%20reaction%20that%20happens%20when%20amniotic%20fluid%20enters%20a%20mothers'%20blood%20stream.%20It%20leads%20to%20heart%20and%20lung%20failure%2C%20and%20massive%20bleeding.%20I%20needed%20143%20units%20of%20blood.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteen-life-support-mom-legal-fight-doctors-brain-dead-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eput%20on%20life%20support%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20then%20transferred%20to%20another%20hospital.%20There%2C%20the%20doctor%20said%20he%20was%20going%20to%20try%20one%20last%20ditch%20effort%20to%20save%20me%20%E2%80%94%20an%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abiomed.com%2Fen-us%2Fpatients-and-caregivers%2Fabout-impella%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Impella%20heart%20pump%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Luckily%2C%20it%20worked%20so%20well%20that%20within%2024%20hours%20I%20was%20able%20to%20start%20coming%20off%20life%20support.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227b9db076-621c-43a6-8b14-9d26b2ef473b%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20brain%20erased%20memories%20of%20pregnancy%20and%20birth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20met%20Callahan%20for%20the%20first%20time%20when%20he%20was%20five%20days%20old.%20My%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FDAMqbkdJgAB%2F%3Fimg_index%3D2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20first%20thought%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20%26quot%3Bthis%20isn't%20my%20baby.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20brain%20just%20couldn't%20process%20all%20that%20had%20happened.%20Callahan%20was%20born%20Wednesday%20afternoon.%20The%20last%20memory%20I%20have%20is%20of%20getting%20my%20nails%20done%20the%20Friday%20before.%20When%20I%20first%20woke%20up%2C%20I%20had%20no%20memory%20of%20any%20prenatal%20appointments.%20It%20was%20like%20my%20brain%20had%20tried%20to%20erase%20anything%20that%20had%20to%20do%20with%20pregnancy%20or%20birth.%20Medically%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ftreatments%2Fshort-term-memory-loss%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20amnesia%20didn't%20make%20sense%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20but%20I'm%20a%20trauma%20therapist%2C%20and%20I%20understood%20that%20my%20brain%20was%20trying%20to%20protect%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20recovery%2C%20I%20felt%20torn%20between%20my%20personal%20and%20professional%20responses%20to%20the%20birth.%20Many%2C%20many%20people%20who%20have%20an%20amniotic%20fluid%20embolism%20don't%20survive%2C%20and%20I%20was%20just%20so%20happy%20to%20be%20alive.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20as%20a%20mental%20health%20professional%20I%20knew%20recovering%20was%20going%20to%20be%20really%2C%20really%20difficult.%20In%20the%20hospital%20I%20told%20my%20husband%20and%20other%20family%20members%20they%20were%20all%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fwhat-is-emdr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egetting%20therapy%20to%20deal%20with%20their%20trauma%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(and%20they%20have).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226bc17fa5-482b-4f98-ab88-f2f76a5a51f8%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20struggled%20to%20bond%20with%20my%20son%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20discharged%20from%20the%20hospital%20when%20Callahan%20was%20two%20weeks%20old.%20I%20was%20so%20mentally%20and%20physically%20exhausted%20that%20I%20wasn't%20interested%20in%20the%20baby.%20My%20family%20members%20would%20ask%20if%20I%20wanted%20to%20feed%20him%2C%20and%20I'd%20say%20yes%2C%20because%20I%20felt%20I%20had%20to.%20Then%2C%20I%20would%20hate%20every%20minute%20of%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELooking%20back%2C%20I%20can%20see%20that%20taking%20those%20feedings%20was%20bonding.%20But%20it%20was%20so%20different%20from%20the%20postpartum%20I'd%20envisioned%20that%20it%20caused%20a%20lot%20of%20emotional%20pain%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20started%20sharing%20my%20story%20about%20six%20months%20after%20Callahan's%20birth.%20Today%2C%20I%20specialize%20in%20treating%20perinatal%20trauma.%20Not%20all%20trauma%20looks%20like%20mine%2C%20but%20all%20birth%20trauma%20can%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20parenting.%20I%20wanted%20to%20create%20a%20community%20where%20people%20could%20talk%20about%20their%20feelings%2C%20without%20needing%20to%20make%20them%20more%20palatable%20to%20others.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228f81be9b-9b59-4bc3-96b0-c83b422aa682%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20still%20grieve%20only%20having%20one%20child%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EToday%20Callahan%20is%205.%20I'm%20still%20devastated%20by%20the%20way%20he%20entered%20the%20world%2C%20but%20we%20talk%20about%20his%20birth%20story.%20In%20our%20first%20family%20picture%2C%20I'm%20on%20a%20ventilator%2C%20and%20Callahan%20knows%20I%20needed%20it%20to%