20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwartz's%202006%20book%20drew%20inspiration%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffaculty.washington.edu%2Fjdb%2F345%2F345%2520Articles%2FIyengar%2520%2526%2520Lepper%2520(2000).pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20found%20that%20shoppers%20in%20a%20grocery%20store%20were%2010%20times%20as%20likely%20to%20purchase%20jam%20after%20sampling%20from%20a%20display%20of%20six%20jam%20varieties%20than%20they%20were%20from%20a%20sampling%20of%2024.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-social-media-online-shopping-30-days-regain-control-productivity-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOnline%20shopping%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20the%20US%20Census%20Bureau%20estimates%20accounts%20for%20roughly%2016%25%20of%20all%20retail%20sales%2C%20theoretically%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20find%20exactly%20what%20we%20are%20looking%20for.%20But%20it%20also%20takes%20the%20jam%20problem%20and%20multiplies%20it%20by%20several%20orders%20of%20magnitude%3A%20We're%20inundated%20with%20hundreds%20and%20thousands%20of%20choices.%20With%20so%20much%20information%20about%20those%20choices%2C%20it%20sometimes%20can%20feel%20impossible%20to%20go%20on.%20What's%20more%2C%20experts%20say%20that%20many%20of%20the%20tools%20we%20rely%20on%20to%20help%20us%20sift%20through%20all%20of%20this%20information%20%E2%80%94%20from%20product%20descriptions%20to%20search%20engines%20to%20e-commerce%20filters%20%E2%80%94%20may%20actually%20be%20making%20the%20process%20even%20harder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20golden%20age%20of%20comparison%20shopping%20isn't%20so%20golden%20after%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20internet%20changed%20not%20just%20how%20we%20shop%20but%20also%20the%20number%20of%20options%20retailers%20can%20offer.%20Superstores%20that%20used%20to%20be%20limited%20by%20their%20square%20footage%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwarehouse-nation-boom-ecommerce-jobs-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecould%20now%20fill%20warehouses%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20thousands%20of%20items%20that%20would%20ship%20straight%20to%20customers'%20doorsteps.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20retail%20landscape%20began%20to%20lean%20toward%20larger%20stores%20with%20more%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJason%20Goldberg%2C%20the%20chief%20commerce-strategy%20officer%20of%20Publicis%20Groupe%2C%20said%20%26quot%3Bcategory%20killers%26quot%3B%20like%20PetSmart%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-tumultuous-history-of-toys-r-us-photos-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EToys%20%26quot%3BR%26quot%3B%20Us%3C%2Fa%3E%20outcompeted%20the%20neighborhood%20mom-and-pop%20pet%20and%20toy%20stores%20of%20yesteryear%20%E2%80%94%20only%20to%20find%20themselves%20losing%20out%20to%20stores%20with%20even%20bigger%20inventories%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-q3-earnings-shoppers-cheaper-items-high-frequency-good-business-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalmart-stock-price-sam-walton-family-wealth-billionaires-retail-strategy-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWalmart%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20history%20of%20retail%2C%20businesses%20with%20larger%20assortments%20have%20come%20in%2C%20and%20they've%20won%20out%20over%20businesses%20with%20small%20assortments%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShoppers%2C%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20love%20the%20convenience%20of%20the%20one-stop%20shop.%20But%20that%20has%20left%20us%20with%20an%20ever-increasing%20number%20of%20options.%20%26quot%3BAmazon's%20doing%20what%20we%20think%20the%20American%20dream%20is%2C%20which%20is%2C%20have%20all%20the%20choice%20in%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Jessecae%20Marsh%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20psychology%20at%20Lehigh%20University%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BBut%20choice%20can%20be%20paralyzing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20problem%2C%20Marsh%20said%2C%20comes%20down%20to%20the%20way%20our%20brain%20makes%20choices.%20When%20shopping%2C%20we%20typically%20start%20by%20looking%20for%20ways%20to%20narrow%20down%20the%20set%20of%20choices%2C%20such%20as%20by%20filtering%20out%20things%20we%20can't%20afford%20or%20that%20aren't%20the%20size%20we%20want.%20Then%20we%20look%20for%20a%20reason%20to%20pick%20one%20of%20the%20remaining%20items%20over%20the%20others.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20try%20to%20make%20decisions%2C%20we%20want%20a%20reason%20behind%20the%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20helps%20explain%20why%20ratings%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Finsider-reviews-expertise-in-product-reviews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereviews%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20become%20such%20a%20popular%20feature%20on%20online%20marketplaces%3A%20When%20we're%20comparing%20two%20similar%20items%2C%20we%20need%20to%20find%20a%20piece%20of%20information%20that%20breaks%20the%20tie.%20A%20higher%20star%20rating%2C%20or%20a%20slate%20of%20glowing%20reviews%20from%20other%20customers%2C%20can%20be%20enough%20to%20do%20the%20trick.%20The%20trouble%20is%20that%20having%20more%20information%20at%20our%20disposal%20isn't%20always%20helpful.%20And%20sometimes%2C%20it%20can%20render%20decision-making%20more%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcognitiveresearchjournal.springeropen.com%2Farticles%2F10.1186%2Fs41235-023-00509-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseries%20of%20experiments%3C%2Fa%3E%20testing%20how%20the%20presence%20of%20diagrams%20influenced%20people's%20ability%20to%20correctly%20answer%20questions%20about%20topics%20like%20managing%20body%20weight%2C%20Marsh%20and%20Samantha%20Kleinberg%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20computer%20science%20at%20the%20Stevens%20Institute%20of%20Technology%2C%20found%20that%20while%20some%20guiding%20information%20could%20be%20helpful%2C%20too%20much%20information%20made%20picking%20the%20right%20answer%20almost%20as%20difficult%20as%20if%20the%20participants%20had%20received%20no%20guiding%20information%20at%20all.%20While%20the%20study%2C%20published%20last%20year%20in%20Cognitive%20Research%3A%20Principles%20and%20Implications%2C%20didn't%20focus%20on%20shopping%2C%20their%20results%20suggested%20that%20the%20more%20information%20we%20wade%20through%20when%20we're%20trying%20to%20make%20a%20decision%2C%20the%20more%20likely%20we%20are%20to%20come%20across%20something%20that%20conflicts%20with%20our%20beliefs%2C%20which%20complicates%20the%20decision-making%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you've%20tried%20an%20Oil%20of%20Olay%20moisturizer%2C%20and%20you%20had%20a%20reaction%20to%20it%2C%20but%20you're%20seeing%20website%20over%20website%20telling%20you%20that's%20the%20best%20one%2C%20you're%20now%20in%20a%20position%20where%20the%20information%20that%20you're%20getting%20doesn't%20match%20information%20that%20you%20hold%20in%20your%20own%20head%2C%26quot%3B%20Marsh%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20conflict%20is%20always%20going%20to%20be%20hard%20for%20people%20because%20they%20don't%20exactly%20know%20how%20to%20resolve%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20doesn't%20help%20that%20the%20tools%20we%20use%20to%20reduce%20overwhelm%20may%20actually%20make%20things%20even%20more%20daunting.%20Raluca%20Ursu%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20marketing%20at%20New%20York%20University's%20Leonard%20N.%20Stern%20School%20of%20Business%2C%20told%20me%20that%20tools%20like%20filtering%2C%20sorting%2C%20and%20using%20recommendations%20could%20bog%20us%20down%20by%20revealing%20new%20factors%20to%20investigate%2C%20which%20leads%20people%20to%20search%20%3Cem%3Emore%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F25674430%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20has%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20be%20less%20satisfied%20with%20their%20choices.%20Search%20engines%20such%20as%20Google%2C%20which%20present%20options%20in%20a%20ranked%20list%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1509%2Fjmr.09.0481%3FjournalCode%3Dmrja%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecan%20also%20lead%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bmaximizer%26quot%3B%20mindset.%20%26quot%3BConsumers%20start%20to%20believe%20they%20can%20find%20'the%20best%20option'%20out%20there%2C%20which%20can%20then%20lead%20to%20additional%20stress%20and%20decision%20paralysis%2C%26quot%3B%20Ursu%20told%20me.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsearch-web-email-google-streaming-online-shopping-broken-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edecline%20of%20Google%20Search%3C%2Fa%3E%20probably%20doesn't%20help%20matters%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUrsu%20has%20studied%20two%20factors%20in%20shopping%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.anderson.ucla.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocument%2F2022-01%2FSearchGaps_UrsuZhangHonka_Dec2021.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esearch%20costs%20and%20search%20fatigue%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BSearch%20costs%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Egenerally%20reflect%20the%20time%20and%20effort%20consumers%20require%20to%20obtain%20information%20about%20a%20product%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20via%20email.%20%26quot%3BHow%20difficult%20is%20it%20to%20determine%20this%20TV's%20price%20and%20technical%20specifications%3F%26quot%3B%20While%20search%20costs%20are%20typically%20much%20smaller%20online%20than%20they%20are%20IRL%2C%20where%20you%20have%20to%20jump%20in%20a%20car%20and%20drive%20to%20a%20store%2C%20search%20fatigue%20grows%20when%20shopping%20online%20because%20there's%20more%20information%20available%20and%20more%20options%20to%20sift%20through.%20Ursu%20guessed%20that%20the%20most%20exhausting%20stage%20of%20shopping%20is%20comparison%20shopping%20%E2%80%94%20when%20people%20pore%20over%20minuscule%20details%20between%20products%20to%20find%20the%20best%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fonline-shopping-coping-mechanism-target-pandemic-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabandon%20their%20shopping%20carts%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20they%20get%20overwhelmed%20by%20search%20fatigue%2C%20it%20can%20come%20back%20to%20bite%20retailers.%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.anderson.ucla.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocument%2F2022-01%2FSearchGaps_UrsuZhangHonka_Dec2021.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20looked%20at%20browsing%20data%20from%20clothing%20shoppers%20in%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20Ursu%20and%20her%20fellow%20researchers%20Qianyun%20Zhang%20and%20Elisabeth%20Honka%20found%20that%20reducing%20search%20fatigue%20by%20half%20led%20to%20a%20slight%20increase%20in%20transactions.%20They%20also%20found%20that%20search%20fatigue%20tended%20to%20affect%20smaller%20retailers%20more%20than%20larger%20ones%20since%20people%20tend%20to%20spend%20all%20their%20energy%20shopping%20at%20larger%20stores%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fashion%2C%20perhaps%20no%20company%20embodies%20the%20paradox%20of%20choice%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstitch-fix-subscription-clothes-review-work-from-home-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStitch%20Fix%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20launched%20in%202011%20with%20a%20counterintuitive%20business%20model%3A%20People%20who%20didn't%20have%20the%20time%20or%20patience%20to%20shop%20could%20undergo%20a%20virtual%20consultation%20with%20one%20of%20the%20firm's%20in-house%20stylists%2C%20then%20receive%20a%20subscription%20box%20filled%20with%20a%20selection%20of%20items%20that%20had%20been%20handpicked%20for%20them.%20It%20worked%3A%20By%202017%2C%20the%20company%20had%20gone%20public%20at%20a%20valuation%20of%20%241.4%20billion%2C%20only%20to%20surge%20to%20a%20%2411%20billion%20market%20cap%20in%20early%202021%2C%20when%20many%20customers%20were%20holed%20up%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaving%20someone%20do%20that%20front-loaded%20effort%2C%20that%20seems%20really%20valuable%2C%26quot%3B%20Marsh%20said.%20It's%20the%20same%20thing%20we%20would%20do%20by%20bringing%20a%20contractor%20into%20a%20house%20to%20ask%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20are%20the%20options%20here%20to%20expand%20this%20bathroom%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20lockdowns%20ended%2C%20the%20company%20decided%20to%20introduce%20an%20option%20where%20customers%20could%20shop%20for%20individual%20items%20from%20categories%20like%20%26quot%3Bjeans%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BLauren%20Ralph%20Lauren%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bworkwear%20under%20%2480.%26quot%3B%20But%20since%20that%20pivot%20away%20from%20its%20core%20business%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstitch-fix-stylists-say-role-company-is-losing-flexibility-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20company%20has%20been%20losing%20customers%3C%2Fa%3E%20every%20year.%20Today%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fsfix-stock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStitch%20Fix%20is%20valued%20at%20%24400%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20just%20a%20fraction%20of%20its%20market%20cap%20at%20its%202017%20initial%20public%20offering.%20Goldberg%2C%20the%20chief%20commerce-strategy%20officer%2C%20said%20it's%20possible%20that%20the%20company's%20struggles%20are%20due%20to%20macro%20factors%2C%20like%20subscription%20fatigue%20and%20a%20sales%20slowdown%20in%20the%20clothes%20business.%20%26quot%3BTwenty%20years%20ago%2C%20you%20spent%206%25%20of%20your%20budget%20on%20clothes%3B%20today%2C%20you%20spend%203%25%20of%20your%20budget%20on%20clothes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20used%20to%20buy%20Stitch%20Fix%20for%20clothes%20to%20wear%20to%20work.%20You%20know%20what%20people%20don't%20do%20anymore%3F%26quot%3B%20Still%2C%20the%20company's%20decline%20raises%20an%2