l-inflation-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecut%20interest%20rates%20by%2050%20basis%20points%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20September%20%E2%80%94%20the%20first%20cut%20in%20four%20years%20and%20one%20twice%20the%20size%20of%20the%20central%20bank's%20typical%2025-point%20increments%20%E2%80%94%20following%20aggressive%20inflation%20fighting%20as%20the%20country%20recovered%20from%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFed%20chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20said%20during%20remarks%20at%20a%20Nashville%20conference%20in%20late%20September%20that%20%26quot%3Bif%20the%20economy%20performs%20as%20expected%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20would%20mean%20two%20more%2025-basis-point%20cuts%20this%20year.%20As%20the%20November%20and%20December%20meetings%20were%20the%20only%20two%20remaining%20in%202024%20at%20the%20time%20of%20those%20remarks%2C%20that%20would%20mean%20standard-size%20cuts%20at%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOverall%2C%20the%20economy%20is%20in%20solid%20shape%2C%26quot%3B%20Powell%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20intend%20to%20use%20our%20tools%20to%20keep%20it%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20several%20data%20releases%20since%20the%20last%20rate%20cut%20that%20suggest%20the%20economy%20is%20in%20good%20shape.%20September's%20jobs%20report%20showed%20unemployment%20fell%20that%20month.%20Recent%20price%20index%20data%20shows%20headline%20inflation%20has%20slowed.%20Real%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgdp-gross-domestic-product-third-quarter-economy-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egross%20domestic%20product%3C%2Fa%3E%20rose%20at%20an%20annualized%20rate%20of%202.8%25%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%2C%20similar%20to%20the%203%25%20growth%20in%20the%20second%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20major%20data%20release%20before%20the%20meeting%20held%20some%20bad%20news%2C%20but%20with%20a%20catch.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foctober-jobs-report-unemployment-rate-nonfarm-payroll-growth-federal-reserve-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOctober's%20jobs%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0published%20this%20past%20Friday%2C%20at%20first%20glance%2C%20showed%20a%20big%20slowdown.%20The%20economy%20added%20just%2012%2C000%20jobs%20over%20the%20month%2C%20far%20below%20the%20forecast%20of%20106%2C000.%20However%2C%C2%A0the%20data%20was%20heavily%20affected%20by%20thousands%20of%20workers%20on%20strike%20at%20Boeing%20and%20other%20companies%2C%20as%20well%20as%C2%A0Hurricanes%C2%A0Helene%20and%20Milton%2C%20which%20likely%20drove%20that%20headline%20figure%20artificially%20down%20and%20did%20not%20reflect%20a%20slowing%20but%20still%20strong%20underlying%20labor%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%2C%20512%2C000%20people%20in%20nonfarm%20industries%20didn't%20work%20because%20of%20bad%20weather%2C%20around%20eight%20times%20the%20previous%2020-year%20October%20average%20of%2063%2C000.%20The%20unemployment%20rate%20%E2%80%94%20for%20which%20BLS%20said%20data%20collection%20was%20less%20affected%20by%20the%20hurricanes%20%E2%80%94%20was%20unchanged%20from%20September's%204.1%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECory%20Stahle%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20Indeed%20Hiring%20Lab%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20October's%20jobs%20report%20%26quot%3Bvalidates%20the%20recent%20rate%20cut%20we%20saw%20from%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20and%20probably%20keeps%20them%20on%20their%20rough%20timeline%20with%20continuing%20to%20offer%20cuts%20to%20keep%20the%20labor%20market%20strong.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20inflation%20is%20near%20the%20Fed's%20target%20rate%20of%202%25.%20The%20personal%20consumption%20expenditures%20price%20index%2C%20which%20is%20closely%20watched%20by%20the%20central%20bank%2C%20increased%202.1%25%20in%20September%20from%20September%202023%2C%20a%20cooldown%20from%20the%20previous%202.3%25.%20Core%20PCE%2C%20which%20excludes%20volatile%20food%20and%20energy%20prices%2C%20rose%20at%202.7%25%20for%20the%20third%20consecutive%20month.%20The%20year-over-year%20rise%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-september-cpi-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsumer%20price%20index%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20also%20slowed%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20cooling%20job%20market%20and%20slowing%20price%20growth%20gives%20the%20Fed%20%26quot%3Bfurther%20confidence%20in%20their%20ability%20to%20cut%20rates%20without%20reigniting%20inflation%2C%26quot%3B%20Julia%20Pollak%2C%20chief%20economist%20at%20ZipRecruiter%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20will%20take%20some%20time%20for%20Americans%20to%20feel%20the%20impact%20of%20September's%20rate%20cut%2C%20along%20with%20any%20upcoming%20ones%2C%20because%20of%20lags%20in%20industries%20like%20housing%2C%20cars%2C%20and%20credit%20cards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBorrowers%20should%20understand%20that%20'falling%20interest%20rates'%20are%20not%20the%20same%20as%20'low%20interest%20rates%2C'%26quot%3B%20Greg%20McBride%2C%20Bankrate's%20chief%20financial%20analyst%2C%20said%20in%20a%20commentary.%20%26quot%3BQuite%20the%20opposite%2C%20as%20interest%20rates%20are%20high%20and%20will%20only%20decline%20to%20'not%20as%20high'%20as%202024%20comes%20to%20a%20close%20and%20we%20move%20into%202025.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPowell%20has%20maintained%20that%20he%20will%20make%20decisions%20solely%20based%20on%20data.%C2%A0Despite%20the%20upcoming%20election%20this%20week%2C%C2%A0he%20has%20repeatedly%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3Esaid%20politics%20remain%20separate%20from%20the%20central%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20job%20is%20to%20support%20the%20economy%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20American%20people%2C%20and%20if%20we%20get%20it%20right%2C%20this%20will%20benefit%20the%20American%20people%20significantly%2C%26quot%3B%20Powell%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cut-trump-fed-powell-reaction-independence-history-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20a%20September%20press%20conference.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20something%20we%20all%20take%20very%2C%20very%20seriously.%20We%20don't%20put%20up%20any%20other%20filters.%20I%20think%20if%20you%20start%20doing%20that%2C%20I%20don't%20know%20where%20you%20stop%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWhat%20are%20your%20financial%20plans%20if%20the%20Fed%20makes%20another%20rate%20cut%3F%20Email%20these%20reporters%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aasheffey%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Easheffey%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amhoff%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Emhoff%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-federal-reserve-election-jerome-powell-inflation-jobs-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1730714401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67254765a0a0cc14f2259e5c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-federal-reserve-election-jerome-powell-inflation-jobs-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It's%20likely%20that%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20will%20cut%20interest%20rates%20by%20a%20quarter%20point%20on%20Thursday%2C%20closing%20out%20a%20busy%20week%20after%20the%20election.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey%2CMadison%20Hoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-federal-reserve-election-jerome-powell-inflation-jobs-2024-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Top%20Hezbollah%20commander%20Abu%20Ali%20Rida%20'eliminated'%20in%20air%20